Injury-replacement signing Mitch Oxborrow will play against the Power, as will triallist Peter Skapetis.
Melbourne-born Skapetis is a 22-year-old attacker who has spent time in England with Queens Park Rangers, Stoke City, Derby County and Dover Athletic.
Knee injuries have hurt his career but Aloisi is keen to give Skapetis an opportunity, believing his speed can create havoc.
Spanish forward Guillermo Torres, who was a second-half substitute in the Roar's 2-0 Heritage Shield win over Lions at Richlands last week, is no longer training with the club.
